1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Ukulele Strumming ]

2
00:00:21,820 --> 00:00:22,854
Listen, pep talk.

3
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:25,556
Big day today.
It's our grand re-re-re-opening.

4
00:00:25,558 --> 00:00:29,360
It's Labor Day weekend,
and it looks like Wonder Wharf
is getting mobbed,

5
00:00:53,586 --> 00:00:56,421
You kids know where
you're supposed to be
while we're gone, right?

6
00:00:56,423 --> 00:00:59,157
Tina,
you're on the grill.
My crotch is itchy.

7
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:00,391
- [ Both Groan ]
- Okay.

8
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:03,227
Are you telling me
as my daughter,
or as my grill cook?

9
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:07,832
Um, as--
Because my grill cook
would never tell me that.

10
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:09,333
Oh.
Also, my daughter...

11
00:01:09,335 --> 00:01:11,702
should probably not say
anything like that to me.

12
00:01:11,704 --> 00:01:12,703
Tell her. Tell your mom.

13
00:01:12,705 --> 00:01:15,440
My crotch is itchy.
Come here, let me see.

14
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:16,407
Linda. Not now.

15
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,542
No, let's all see it.
No.

16
00:01:17,544 --> 00:01:20,578
I'm just not sure
if I'll be any good
on the grill...

17
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:22,447
with just one free hand.

18
00:01:22,449 --> 00:01:24,715
Okay, I'm just going to
keep moving here.

19
00:01:24,717 --> 00:01:26,350
Louise,
you're working the counter.

20
00:01:26,352 --> 00:01:27,885
I put your little step stool
back here.

21
00:01:27,887 --> 00:01:30,488
But do not alter anything
on the chalkboard.

22
00:01:30,490 --> 00:01:32,423
What if I think of
something better--

23
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:34,358
which would be
almost impossible
not to do.

24
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:38,796
You will not think
of something better, because
"New Bacon-ings" is perfect.

25
00:01:38,798 --> 00:01:40,731
It's hilarious. Right?

26
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:42,400
You know what?
I'm taking the chalk.

27
00:01:42,402 --> 00:01:43,501
[ Whispering ]
Like I don't have chalk.

28
00:01:43,503 --> 00:01:46,604
Gene, you're outside,
nicely offering people
a free sample, all right?

29
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:49,807
I'm on it!
But people coming out
of the crematorium next door,

30
00:01:49,809 --> 00:01:52,777
people obviously
in mourning--
Yeah?

31
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,178
Don't offer them samples.

32
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:57,715
Dad, when I'm in character
out there, I get in a zone!

33
00:01:57,717 --> 00:02:00,885
I can't keep track
of who's in mourning
and who isn't.

34
00:02:00,887 --> 00:02:02,920
Just-- Anyone with an urn--

35
00:02:02,922 --> 00:02:04,255
Yeah?
Leave 'em alone!

36
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:06,257
I know you think
it's the Gene show out there,

37
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:31,174
Oh. Now my rash
smells like bacon,

38
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:32,742
and it doesn't itch anymore.

39
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:34,678
I think we're going to be okay.

40
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,179
Okay, Tina, thank you.

41
00:18:36,181 --> 00:18:38,148
Dad, is the restaurant
gonna close?

42
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:41,151
[ Sighs ]
I don't know, Louise.
We're almost broke.

43
00:18:41,153 --> 00:18:45,188
The whole town
thinks we're cannibals,
and I forgot our anniversary.

44
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:47,557
You'd have been better off
with Hugo, Linda.

45
00:18:47,559 --> 00:18:49,626
Bob, please.
No, it's true.

46
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:51,661
I can't even satisfy you
with my kisses.

47
00:18:51,663 --> 00:18:54,598
Sorry, kids.
No problem.
Thanks for the info.

48
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:57,234
Oh, Bobby!
Now you listen to me.

